sequenceDiagram
    participant BG as Background Tick Thread
    participant AA as AutonomousAgent
    participant FL as Fleet (4 Assets)
    participant AD as AnomalyDetector
    participant MCP as MCP Server
    participant MT as Metrics Module

    loop every 1.2s while enabled
        AA->>FL: for each asset: snapshot()
        FL-->>AA: telemetry per asset
        AA->>AD: detect(snapshot)
        AD-->>AA: findings (rule-triggered only are actionable)

        alt genuine threshold breach found
            AA->>AA: mark asset busy, spawn incident thread
            activate AA
            AA->>AA: state = DETECTED (log narrated entry)
            AA->>MCP: run_rca_pipeline(query, use_llm=true)
            MCP-->>AA: cited synthesis + citations
            AA->>AA: state = DIAGNOSING (log entry)
            AA->>FL: asset.apply_fix()
            AA->>AA: state = FIXING (log entry)
            loop poll until recovered or timeout
                AA->>FL: asset.snapshot()
                FL-->>AA: status
            end
            AA->>AA: state = VALIDATING (log recovery)
            AA->>MT: record resolved incident (elapsed_seconds)
            alt failure mode recurred >= 2x
                AA->>AD: tighten THRESHOLDS[signal] fleet-wide
                AA->>AA: state = OPTIMIZING (log threshold change)
            end
            AA->>AA: release busy lock, state = MONITORING
            deactivate AA
        else no breach, asset idle too long, auto_inject on
            AA->>FL: inject_fault(random_mode)
            Note over AA,FL: keeps a walk-away demo alive
        end
    end

    Note over AA: Multiple incident threads can run concurrently across different assets - this is what makes it fleet-scale, not a single demo machine.
